Making the config: ~/.gitconfig:
 git config --global user.name <name>
 git config --global user.email <email>

Cloning from the web repo:
 git clone https://github.com/carambalada/notes.git
 # it makes the objects:
 # notes/
 #  .git/
 #  git 

Making a project from scrach:
 mkdir tar-bar
 cd tar-bar
 git init
 # edit a_file
 git add a_file
 git commit -m "comment"

 # make a repo: https://github.com/carambalada/tar-bar.git
 git remote add origin https://github.com/carambalada/tar-bar.git
 git push -u origin master

Getting info:
 # diff:
 git diff [--cached]
 # status:
 git status
 # log:
 git log [-p]

### Revise it ###
 pull request
 pull request again
 merge with the master
